==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Canon bone
<hw>Can"on bone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F. <ets>canon</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>canon</ets> a rule. See <er>canon</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The shank bone, or great bone above the fetlock, in the fore and
hind legs of the horse and allied animals, corresponding to the middle
metacarpal or metatarsal bone of most mammals. See
<er>Horse</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

